abstract: Candidates are leaving potential Republican converts without options.
snippet: Candidates are leaving potential Republican converts without options.
lead_paragraph: Under President Trump, a small slice of America’s electorate seeks a reason to call the Democratic Party home for the very first time. But without adequate hospitality to welcome them, they will disappear quickly.

headline_main: Why Are Democrats Jilting G.O.P. Voters Who Want to Like Them?

lead_paragraph: Gail Collins: Bret, where should we start? Democratic debate? Impeachment? Mideast crisis? Rudy Giuliani? Actually, as a New Yorker I always figured that someday Rudy would do something even more outrageous than the time he called a news conference to announce he was separating from his wife before he told said spouse. But I did not imagine it would include sleazy Ukrainians and Joe Biden’s son.

headline_main: Fiona Hill, Hunter Biden, LeBron James: Your Tuesday Briefing

abstract: We asked veterans of political debates for the advice they would give to each of the Democratic hopefuls onstage Tuesday.
snippet: We asked veterans of political debates for the advice they would give to each of the Democratic hopefuls onstage Tuesday.
lead_paragraph: As part of our 2020 debate coverage, we are asking political debate coaches and experts to tell us what each candidate needs to do to win, and what advice they would give those onstage. Then we will ask the experts afterward how the candidates did.

headline_main: Which Candidates Will Win Tonight’s Democratic Debate? Six Experts Offer Tips
byline_original: By Reid J. Epstein and Lisa Lerer

abstract: The 2020 Democratic hopefuls will debate in a state that has voted for the winning presidential candidate every time since 1944, with one exception.
snippet: The 2020 Democratic hopefuls will debate in a state that has voted for the winning presidential candidate every time since 1944, with one exception.
lead_paragraph: As the 2020 Democratic candidates descend Tuesday on Westerville, Ohio, a northern suburb of Columbus, for the fourth presidential debate, here are 12 fast facts about politics and the economy in the Buckeye State that could help shape the upcoming election.

abstract: Mr. Biden in recent days has been more forceful in defending his family and denouncing the president. Some voters and Democratic officials think he should do more.
snippet: Mr. Biden in recent days has been more forceful in defending his family and denouncing the president. Some voters and Democratic officials think he should do more.
lead_paragraph: WESTERVILLE, Ohio — In the last few days, Joseph R. Biden Jr. has unveiled a new government ethics plan and vowed that his family members would do no business overseas during a Biden presidency. His son, Hunter Biden, said he would step down from his role with a Chinese investment firm, and sat for his first television interview of the campaign. And in Iowa, the elder Mr. Biden delivered a fist-pounding diatribe against President Trump, casting him as the embodiment of public corruption.

abstract: President Trump’s erratic moves are letting Russia seize the role of peacemaker — and deal-maker — in Syria.
snippet: President Trump’s erratic moves are letting Russia seize the role of peacemaker — and deal-maker — in Syria.
lead_paragraph: MOSCOW — These have been disastrous weeks for American foreign policy, a popular presenter on Russia’s state television told viewers on Sunday night with an I-told-you-so smirk.

abstract: Republicans who cast the impeachment inquiry as yet another partisan character assassination may find it difficult to rally the same kind of unified support that helped Brett Kavanaugh.
snippet: Republicans who cast the impeachment inquiry as yet another partisan character assassination may find it difficult to rally the same kind of unified support that helped Brett Kavanaugh.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Some of President Trump’s most relentless defenders are expressing a sense of déjà vu over the impeachment inquiry currently underway.
